        "created_at": "2025-03-05T21:53:12.352Z",
        "cooked": "<p>Upon updating to Signal Desktop 7.45.0 ⁨production⁩ (Intel) on MacOS, my language was selected as “system - english” but the UI is shown in Dutch. Also after applying and rebooting,</p>\n<p>Manually setting to English fixes the problem, however, when switching back again to “English - system language” it shows Dutch again.</p>\n<p>My system language is indeed English and not Dutch, and the detected language is shown correctly. It is however not the actual UI language applied</p>\n<p><div class=\"lightbox-wrapper\"><a class=\"lightbox\" href=\"https://community.signalusers.org/uploads/db3609/original/3X/2/b/2b69a4c706bab29962d06f9fb60d11dbfc5b0510.png\" data-download-href=\"https://community.signalusers.org/uploads/db3609/2b69a4c706bab29962d06f9fb60d11dbfc5b0510\" title=\"Screenshot 2025-03-05 at 22.41.12\"><img src=\"https://community.signalusers.org/uploads/db3609/optimized/3X/2/b/2b69a4c706bab29962d06f9fb60d11dbfc5b0510_2_329x500.png\" alt=\"Screenshot 2025-03-05 at 22.41.12\" data-base62-sha1=\"6c2S2VV1U9pz7Q5YsId1PaAuPgk\" width=\"329\" height=\"500\" srcset=\"https://community.signalusers.org/uploads/db3609/optimized/3X/2/b/2b69a4c706bab29962d06f9fb60d11dbfc5b0510_2_329x500.png, https://community.signalusers.org/uploads/db3609/optimized/3X/2/b/2b69a4c706bab29962d06f9fb60d11dbfc5b0510_2_493x750.png 1.5x, https://community.signalusers.org/uploads/db3609/optimized/3X/2/b/2b69a4c706bab29962d06f9fb60d11dbfc5b0510_2_658x1000.png 2x\" data-dominant-color=\"323233\"><div class=\"meta\"><svg class=\"fa d-icon d-icon-far-image svg-icon\" aria-hidden=\"true\"><use href=\"#far-image\"></use></svg><span class=\"filename\">Screenshot 2025-03-05 at 22.41.12</span><span class=\"informations\">744×1130 43.1 KB</span><svg class=\"fa d-icon d-icon-discourse-expand svg-icon\" aria-hidden=\"true\"><use href=\"#discourse-expand\"></use></svg></div></a></div><br>\n<div class=\"lightbox-wrapper\"><a class=\"lightbox\" href=\"https://community.signalusers.org/uplo